model_explanation: the focus "ROB" indicates that grapes were given only to Rob, which entails that Rob did not receive apples.
the focus "SUE" means only Sue received grapes, so giving grapes to Tom would contradict that statement.
focusing on "ELLEN" means only Ellen got grapes, but this does not entail or contradict whether Rob was given grapes (it is independent information).
focusing on "MARY" for grapes does not say anything about whether she also received bananas, so the two statements are independent.
focusing on "SUE" for apples means only Sue got apples, so Bill did not get apples. This entails the second statement.
focusing on "TOM" for apples means that apples were only given to Tom and therefore saying he also got grapes contradicts that restrictive condition.
focusing on "BILL" for bananas means Bill only got bananas, so he did not get grapes, which entails the second statement.
focusing on "ELLEN" for apples means only Ellen got apples, so saying Rob also got apples contradicts that.
focusing on "SUE" for bananas means only Sue got bananas, so giving bananas to Tom contradicts that.
focusing on "MARY" for grapes tells us that only Mary received grapes, but it does not say anything about Bill, making the two statements independent.
